el are licensed to practice medicine in any other state of the United States or any province of Canada, have satisfactorily completed an internship of not less than one year in the United States, Canada, or Puerto Rico in a hospital approved for that pur
pose by the American medical association, have satisfactorily completed three years of postgraduate residency training, or its equivalent, in their particular specialty in a hospital approved for that purpose by the American medical association, and can 
read, write, speak, and understand the English language. Proof of said requirements shall be submitted to and approved or disapproved by the executive director.
