ection 12-36-102.5, C.R.S., have completed an approved internship of at least one year as defined in section 12-36-102.5, C.R.S., and, within nine months after first being employed, pass the examinations approved by the Colorado medical board under the p
rovisions of the "Colorado Medical Practice Act" and the national board of medical examiners, the national board of examiners for osteopathic physicians and surgeons, or the federation of state medical boards, or their successor organizations, on subject
s relating to the basic sciences, are able to read, write, speak, and understand the English language, and, in the case of personnel who are not citizens of the United States, become citizens within the minimum period of time within which the particular 
