\par }\pard \s8 \qj\sb180\sa180\fi360 {\*\bkmkstart 17-1-115.5}{\*\bkmkend 17-1-115.5}{\b\fs24 17-1-115.5. Prison sexual assault prevention program.
\par }\pard \s9 \qj {\v\fs8 Statute text
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (1) The department shall develop, with respect to sexual assaults that occur in correctional facilities operated by or pursuant to a contract with 
the department, policies and procedures to:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (a) Require disciplinary action for employees who fail to report incidences of sexual assault to the inspector general appointed pursuant to sectio
n 17-1-103.8;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) Require the inspector general or the department of corrections investigator, whichever is appropriate, after completing an investigation for se
xual assault, to submit the findings to the district attorney with jurisdiction over the facility in which the alleged sexual assault occurred;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) Prohibit retaliation and disincentives for reporting sexual assaults;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (d) Provide, in situations in which there is reason to believe that a sexual assault has occurred, reasonable and appropriate measures to ensure vi
ctim safety by separating the victim from the assailant, if known;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (e) Ensure the confidentiality of prison rape complaints and protection of inmates who make complaints of prison rape;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (f) Provide acute trauma care for sexual assault victims, including but not limited to treatment of injuries, HIV/AIDS prophylactic measures, and t
esting for sexually transmitted diseases;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (g) Provide, at intake and periodically thereafter, department-approved, easy-to-understand information developed by the department on sexual assau
lt prevention, treatment, reporting, and counseling in consultation with community groups with expertise in sexual assault prevention, treatment, reporting, and counseling;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (h) Provide sexual-assault-specific training to department mental health professionals and all employees who have direct contact with inmates regar
ding treatment and methods of prevention and investigation;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (i) Provide confidential mental health counseling for victims of sexual assault;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (j) Monitor victims of sexual assault for suicidal impulses, post-traumatic stress disorder, depression, and other mental health consequences resul
ting from the sexual assault; and
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (k) Require termination of an employee who engages in a sexual assault on or sexual conduct with an inmate consistent with constitutional due proce
ss protections and state personnel laws and rules.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (2) Investigation of a sexual assault shall be conducted by investigators trained in the investigation of sex crimes. The investigation shall inclu
de, but need not be limited to, use of forensic rape kits, questioning of suspects and witnesses, and gathering and preserving relevant evidence.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (3) The department shall annually report the data that it is required to compile and report to the federal bureau of justice statistics as required
 by the federal "Prison Rape Elimination Act of 2003", Pub.L. 108-79, as amended, to the judiciary committees of the house of representatives and the senate, or any successor committees.
\par }\pard \s9 \qj {\v\fs8 History
