\par }\pard \s9 \qj {\v\fs8 Statute text
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (1) On or before December 1, 2001, the department shall issue a request for proposal for the construction and operation of a private contract priso
n to serve as a preparole and revocation center, that shall be a level III facility, as described in section 17-1-104.3 (1) (a) (III).
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (2) The prison described in subsection (1) of this section shall contain at least three hundred beds and incarcerate any of the following:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (a) Inmates who have not been convicted of a crime of violence as defined in section 18-1.3-406, C.R.S., and who have no more than nineteen months 
remaining until such inmate's parole eligibility date;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) Inmates who have been convicted of a crime of violence as defined in section 18-1.3-406, C.R.S., and who have no more than nine months remainin
g until such inmate's parole eligibility date; or
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) Offenders whose parole has been revoked; except that such incarceration shall be for no more than one hundred eighty days.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (3) In addition to the preparole release and revocation facility described in subsections (1) and (2) of this section, the department has the autho
rity to operate community return-to-custody facilities and provide other support and monitoring services as a revocation facility for the placement of nonviolent parolees whose parole is revoked pursuant to section 17-2-103 (11) (b) (III) under the follo
wing conditions:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (a) The facilities shall be limited to the placement of nonviolent parolees whose parole is revoked pursuant to section 17-2-103 (11) (b) (III);
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) The scope of the facilities' programming shall be limited to services and monitoring that address the failure of a nonviolent parolee whose par
ole is revoked pursuant to section 17-2-103 (11) (b) (III) and will allow for limited performance-based access to the community. A request for proposals for such services and monitoring shall be issued by the department on or before August 31, 2003, and 
the contracts awarded by November 2003.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) The department may assess and collect fees from parolees placed in the facility pursuant to section 17-2-103 (11) (b) (III).
