\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (1) (a) The director of the division of adult parole shall contemporaneously send written notice to the chief executive officer of the municipality
 and the city council or board of trustees of the municipality in which the division intends to operate the branch parole office.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) If the site of the branch parole office that the division intends to operate is not located within a municipality, the director of the division
 shall send written notice to the board of county commissioners of the county in which the division intends to operate the branch parole office.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) For purposes of this section:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (I) "Actual acquisition" means the legal process necessary to vest the department of corrections with fee title or a new leasehold interest in real
 estate that the division of adult parole intends to operate as a branch parole office in a new location.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (II) "Branch parole office" means any real estate in this state that the division of adult parole, on behalf of the department of corrections, may 
acquire by purchase, leasehold, or other method for the purpose of operating an office to perform any function required or permitted by this title concerning parolee interview, reporting, testing, screening, and supervision.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (2) A municipality or county notified pursuant to subsection (1) of this section may notify its residents and invite public review and comment on t
he division's selection of the branch parole office site through public meeting, public hearing, or any other public forum deemed appropriate by the municipality or county.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (3) Nothing in this section shall be construed to hinder or prohibit the department of corrections, division of adult parole, from engaging in the 
