 provides for no possibility of parole for persons sentenced to life imprisonment following conviction for class 1 felony offenses occurring during the period from July 1, 1990, until September 19, 1991, is abrogated by this later enactment. Thus, \'a7 1
6-11-103 (1)(b) (now \'a7 18-1.3-1201 (1)(b)), as amended by House Bill 91S-1001, controls parole eligibility for convictions and sentences to life imprisonment based on class 1 felony offenses occurring on or after September 20, 1991, and \'a7 16-11-802
 (1)(b) (now \'a7 18-1.3-1302 (1)(b)) controls parole eligibility for class 1 felony offenses occurring during the period from July 1, 1990 until September 19, 1991. People v. District Court, 834 P.2d 236 (Colo. 1992).
\par }\pard \s17 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub  }{\b\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub Prisoner's parole eligibility date is determined by the date on which th
