\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub  so the inmate's punishment is not increased by withholding earned time from the inmate for not participating in sex offender treatment. Reeves v. Colo. Dept. of Corr., 155 P.3d 648 (Colo. Ap
p. 2007).
\par }\pard \s17 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub  }{\b\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub The creation and distribution of credits to be applied against an inmate
's sentence are matters committed to the authority of the legislature;}{\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub  trial court orders do not prevail over the letter and intent of statutory provisions adopted by the general 
