\par }\pard \s17 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub  }{\b\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub Mandamus relief under C.R.C.P. 106 is available to challenge the parole 
board's actions if it has failed to exercise its statutory duties.}{\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub  Although plaintiff did not expressly seek mandamus relief pursuant to C.R.C.P. 106, the gravamen of his complain
t was that the parole board's failure to consider any events or circumstances prior to plaintiff's incarceration was in direct violation of statutory guidelines for parole. Under these circumstances, the trial court had jurisdiction to address the merits
 of the complaint. Fraser v. Colo. Bd. of Parole, 931 P.2d 560 (Colo. App. 1996).
\par }\pard \s8 \qj\sb180\sa180\fi360 {\*\bkmkstart 17-22.5-404.5}{\*\bkmkend 17-22.5-404.5}{\b\fs24 17-22.5-404.5. Presumption of parole - drug offenders - repeal.
\par }\pard \s9 \qj {\v\fs8 Statute text
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (1) There shall be a presumption, subject to the final discretion of the parole board, in favor of granting parole to an inmate who has reached his
 or her parole eligibility date and who:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (a) Is serving a sentence for which the controlling term of incarceration is based on a felony possession or use offense described in section 18-18
-404, or section 18-18-405, C.R.S., as it existed prior to August 11, 2010;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) Has not incurred a class I code of penal discipline violation within the last twelve months or a class II code of penal discipline violation wi
thin the last three months;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) Is program-compliant;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (d) Was not convicted of, and has not previously been convicted of, a felony crime described in section 18-3-303, 18-3-305, 18-3-306, or 18-6-701; 
sections 18-7-402 to 18-7-407; or section 18-12-102 or 18-12-109, C.R.S.; or a felony crime listed in section 24-4.1-302 (1), C.R.S.; and
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (e) Does not have an active felony or immigration detainer.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (2) Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, an inmate who is eligible for the presumption in subsection (1) of this section shall hav
e a parole release hearing within ninety days after becoming eligible for the presumption in subsection (1) of this section.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (3) If the parole board grants parole to an inmate pursuant to subsection (1) of this section, the parole board shall require as a condition of par
ole that the parolee participate in substance abuse treatment consistent with the assessed treatment need of the parolee.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (4) (a) The chairperson of the parole board shall provide a report to the judiciary committees of the house of representatives and the senate, or a
ny successor committees, by January 30, 2012, and by each January 30 thereafter regarding the impact of this section on the department of corrections' population and public safety.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) This subsection (4) is repealed, effective February 1, 2016.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (5) Nothing in this section shall be construed to limit the discretion of the parole board in considering the statutory release guidelines in secti
on 17-22.5-404 or the administrative release guidelines developed pursuant to section 17-22.5-107 (1) in making a decision regarding an inmate's application for release to parole.
\par }\pard \s9 \qj {\v\fs8 History
