\par }\pard \s9 \qj {\v\fs8 Statute text
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (1) (a) Subject to the prior approval of the correctional industries advisory committee acting by resolution in accordance with the provisions of s
ection 17-24-104 (5) and from both houses of the general assembly acting either by bill or joint resolution, the division may, in accordance with the requirements of subsection (2) of this section, authorize and issue revenue bonds in an amount not to ex
ceed one million dollars in the aggregate for expenses of the division.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) All bonds issued by the division shall provide that:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (I) No holder of any such bond may compel the state or any subdivision thereof to exercise its appropriation or taxing power; and
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (II) The bond does not constitute a debt of the state and is payable only from the net revenues allocated to the division for expenses as designate
d in such bond.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (2) Any bonds issued pursuant to the terms of this section may be sold at public or private sale. If bonds are to be sold at a public sale, the div
ision shall advertise the sale in such manner as the general assembly authorizes by bill or joint resolution. All bonds issued pursuant to the terms of this section shall be sold at a price not less than the par value thereof, together with all accrued i
nterest to the date of delivery.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (3) Notwithstanding any provisions of the law to the contrary, all bonds issued pursuant to this section are negotiable.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (4) Bonds issued under this section shall be valid and binding obligations, regardless of whether, prior to the delivery thereof and payment theref
or, any or all of the persons whose signatures appear thereon have ceased to serve in their official capacities.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (5) (a) Except as otherwise provided in a resolution authorizing bonds pursuant to the provisions of section 17-24-104 (5), all bonds of the same i
ssue under this section shall have a prior and paramount lien on the net revenues pledged therefor.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) Bonds of the same issue or series issued under this section shall be equally and ratably secured, without priority by reason of number, date, s
ale, execution, or delivery, by a lien on the net revenue pledged in accordance with the terms of the resolution authorizing the bonds.
\par }\pard \s9 \qj {\v\fs8 History
