\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (1) As used in this section, unless the context otherwise requires:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (a) (Deleted by amendment, L. 2002, p. 218, \'a7 1, effective April 3, 2002.)
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) "State agency" means this state or any department or other agency of the state, but not including the department of transportation.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) "Surplus state property" means any equipment and supplies no longer having any use to the state or any state agency.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (2) The director shall promulgate rules to be utilized by the division in governing:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (a) The sale or disposal of surplus state property by public auction, competitive sealed bidding, or daily warehouse sales; and
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) (Deleted by amendment, L. 2002, p. 218, \'a7 1, effective April 3, 2002.)
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) The circumstances under which a public employee may purchase surplus state property.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (d) (Deleted by amendment, L. 2011, (HB 11-1301), ch. 297, p. 1424, \'a7 16, effective August 10, 2011.)
