\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) Repealed.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) (Deleted by amendment, L. 2002, p. 218, \'a7 1, effective April 3, 2002.)
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (3) Such rules shall include, but shall not be limited to:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (a) The preparation of a perpetual inventory of surplus state property collected by the division;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (a.5) A procedure to inform all state agencies of the availability of such surplus state property;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) (Deleted by amendment, L. 2002, p. 218, \'a7 1, effective April 3, 2002.)
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) Procedures coordinating, to the extent possible, the programs administered by the division under section 17-24-106 with the division's responsi
bility with respect to surplus state property;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (d) A procedure whereby surplus state property which is not sold or otherwise disposed of within six months after being received by the division sh
all be disposed of as soon as possible thereafter.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (4) Any moneys used to cover the administrative costs of the transfer of responsibilities with respect to surplus state property from the departmen
t of administration to the department of corrections shall be transmitted to the state treasurer, who shall credit the same to the surplus property fund, which fund is hereby created, and such fund shall be subject to appropriation by the general assembl
y for the purposes of this section.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (5) Any moneys in any accounts or funds administered by the department of administration that are derived from the administration of part 4 of arti
cle 82 of title 24, C.R.S., shall be transferred to the surplus property fund.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (6) The division may assess fees from the disposer or recipient of any surplus state property, which fees shall be limited to reasonable administra
