\par }\pard \s8 \qj\sb180\sa180\fi360 {\*\bkmkstart 17-24-124}{\*\bkmkend 17-24-124}{\b\fs24 17-24-124. Inmate disaster relief program - legislative declaration.
\par }\pard \s9 \qj {\v\fs8 Statute text
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (1) The general assembly finds that inmates housed in certain prison facilities throughout the state form a labor pool that could be safely utilize
d to fight forest fires, help with flood relief, and assist in the prevention of or clean up after other natural or man-made disasters.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (2) As used in this section, unless the context otherwise requires, "disaster" means the occurrence or imminent threat of widespread or severe dama
ge, injury, or loss of life or property resulting from any natural cause or cause of human origin, but "disaster" does not include any hazardous substance incident, oil spill or other contamination, epidemic, air pollution, blight, drought, infestation, 
explosion, civil disturbance, or hostile military or paramilitary action.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (3) There is hereby established in the division the inmate disaster relief program, referred to in this section as the "program". The purpose of th
e program shall be to establish one or more inmate disaster relief crews composed of inmates from minimum restrictive, or minimum security facilities. An inmate shall receive an additional amount of earned time pursuant to section 17-22.5-405 in the amou
nt of one day of earned time for every day spent at the site of a disaster. An inmate disaster relief crew may be utilized by the state or by local or federal governmental agencies that apply to the division for assistance.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (4) The executive director shall promulgate rules governing the program including but not limited to:
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (a) The inmates who are eligible to participate in the program;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (b) Types of disasters to which an inmate disaster relief crew may be sent;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (c) The security measures that are required to prevent escapes and protect the public;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (d) The procedures that must be followed before an inmate disaster relief crew may be utilized;
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (e) The fees that may be charged by the division for the provision of services by an inmate disaster relief crew; and
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (f) The compensation that may be paid to inmates participating in the program.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (5) The division is authorized to purchase equipment and obtain necessary training for any inmate disaster relief crews.
\par }\pard \s29 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f0\fs24\cf0\nosupersub (6) The department is authorized to solicit, accept, and expend grants, donations, gifts, and other moneys to defer the costs of equipping and trai
ning one or more inmate disaster relief crews. The program shall not be implemented or made available to other agencies until sufficient moneys are available from appropriations, grants, donations, gifts, and other moneys to cover the costs of equipping 
and training at least one inmate disaster relief crew.
\par }\pard \s9 \qj {\v\fs8 History
