fter the trial on the new charge,}{\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub  there is no abuse of discretion by proceeding with the hearing before disposition of the criminal charge. People v. Harrison, 771 P.2d 23 (Colo. 
