\par }\pard \s17 \qj\sb180\fi360 {\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub  }{\b\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub The phrase "extended limits on his confinement" refers to geographic and
 time limits placed on the offender beyond those placed by incarceration in a correctional facility.}{\b0\i0\ul0\strike0\v0\expnd0\expndtw0\outl0\shad0\f1\fs20\cf0\nosupersub  People v. Perea, 74 P.3d 326 (Colo. App. 2002).
